headline: Murder at Dawn: A Top Executive’s Final Moments in Manhattan
summary: NEW YORK—UnitedHealth Group’s annual investor day began much like any other corporate event.  There was breakfast and then around 8 a.m. Wednesday the collection of investors, executives and Wall Street analysts filed into a capacious third-floor ballroom at the  Hilton Hotel  in Midtown Manhattan to hear upbeat presentations about the company’s future.  Brian Thompson,  chief executive of UnitedHealthcare, the largest U.S. health insurer, had been steps from the Hilton’s entrance at 6:44 a.m. when an assassin wearing a dark hoodie and gray backpack stepped from behind a parked car in the predawn darkness, calmly pursued him for a few steps, and then shot him with a 9-millimeter pistol.
